id: pm-qeu1
title: MCP pm_update --comment string crashes with 'values.map is not a function'
description: "Calling pm_update via MCP with options.comment='some text' (string, not array) crashes with `values.map is not a function`. Likely the same root cause as the tags-as-CSV fix (pm-1jcw from session 10) - comment/note/learning fields expect arrays and the MCP normalizer doesn't promote scalars. Workaround: call via CLI `pm comments <id> <text>`."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: agent-ux,mcp,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-16T21:58:02.396Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-16T23:13:08.097Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: MCP pm_update accepts string scalars for comment/note/learning and promotes them to arrays; new test covers the normalization.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Fixed by MCP option normalization and regression coverage for scalar comment/note/learning.
expected_result: MCP pm_update accepts scalar log fields without values.map crashes.
actual_result: "handleRequest(pm_update) accepts scalar comment, note, and learning; linked test and release gate passed."
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-16T21:59:05.363Z",maintainer-agent,"Fixed in this session: src/mcp/server.ts normalizeOptionsArrays now promotes scalar strings to single-element arrays for comment/note/learning/reminder/event/dep/depRemove/file/doc/test/unset/add/remove/addGlob/migrate/envSet/envClear fields when the CLI expects arrays. The running MCP server uses the old build until restarted."
  "2026-05-16T23:12:21.685Z",codex-agent,"Evidence: src/mcp/server.ts already promoted scalar MCP log options; regression now exercises pm_update with scalar comment, note, and learning through handleRequest. Linked test passed via pm test --run and focused suite; full coverage/release gate also passed."
